NeuroPrep UI Build Notes for Habit Loop System

1. Daily Streak System
- Add a top dashboard streak card with flame icon, current streak, longest streak, and streak freeze count.
- Add a streak milestone strip with 3d, 7d, 14d, 30d markers.
- Add a streak warning banner when the reminder message says the streak is at risk.
- Add a streak freeze chip/button state only if you want manual consumption later.

2. XP and Level System
- Add an XP summary card near the hero section.
- Show level number, level title, total XP, and XP needed for next level.
- Add a horizontal animated XP bar with milestone labels.
- Add a reward burst animation when XP changes.

3. Daily Challenges
- Show a dedicated "Daily Challenges" block on the dashboard.
- Each challenge needs title, description, reward XP, progress count, and a progress bar.
- Completed challenges should switch to a success state with confetti or glow animation.
- Add a compact mobile version with stacked cards.

4. Achievement Badges
- Add a badge gallery with locked/unlocked states.
- Show recently unlocked badges in a smaller "latest rewards" row.
- Each badge card should support icon, badge name, unlocked date, and rarity styling.
- Add a badge modal or drawer if you want richer history later.

5. Leaderboards
- Add tabs for weekly/global/class/friends UI even if only weekly/global are wired now.
- Each row needs rank, username, XP, level, streak, and avatar placeholder.
- Top 3 should have premium card treatment with gold/silver/bronze styling.
- Add empty state for users with no XP recorded yet.

6. Study Missions
- Add a mission card with mission name, description, reward XP, optional badge reward, and a large progress bar.
- Show mission status chips: active, completed.
- Add a carousel or stacked timeline if multiple missions are shown later.

7. Smart Reminders
- Add a notification banner or compact callout near the top of the dashboard.
- Show reminder urgency with subtle color changes.
- Keep dismiss action optional; backend currently provides the message only.

8. Reward Animations
- Add confetti burst on challenge completion.
- Add XP float-up numbers on event completion.
- Add flame pulse on streak increase.
- Add badge unlock modal animation.
- Add subtle sound toggle in settings if you later wire sound effects.

9. Progress Visualization
- Add mastery progress cards with labels and animated progress bars.
- Add circular completion rings for streak, mission, and level progress if desired.
- Use clear percentages and completion counts, not only visuals.

10. AI Encouragement
- Add an encouragement callout card with AI icon and short supportive message.
- Add a rotating message area on the dashboard hero if you want stronger habit reinforcement.
- Keep this text short; it should feel like reinforcement, not a paragraph.

11. Responsive Dashboard Adjustments
- On mobile, order should be:
  streak/xp summary
  reminder
  daily challenges
  mission
  leaderboard
  achievements
- On desktop, put challenges and mission left, leaderboard and badges right.

12. Visual Style Guidance
- Use glass cards with stronger accent borders on completed items.
- Use flame/orange for streaks, cyan for XP, violet for achievements, amber for leaderboard.
- Keep animations smooth and short. Avoid heavy motion on every rerender.

13. Backend Hooks Already Added
- Study session completion updates streak and XP.
- Quiz submission updates XP and question counts.
- Mock submission updates XP and question counts.
- Game score submission updates XP.
- Manual event endpoint exists for future lesson/flashcard UI hooks.

